Answer: Step 1: Start from 2-fluoro-6-bromobenzoic acid and esterify to ethyl 2-fluoro-6-bromobenzoate. | Step 2: Convert the aryl bromide to the thiol (e.g., thiourea substitution/deprotection) to give ethyl 2-fluoro-6-mercaptobenzoate. | Step 3: In parallel, acylate the bicyclic amine fragment with bromoacetyl bromide to form the corresponding 2-bromoacetamide. | Step 4: Perform SNAr of the thiolate from ethyl 2-fluoro-6-mercaptobenzoate onto the electron-poor chlorofluoro fused azaaryl chloride core to install the aryl thioether core. | Step 5: N-alkylate the ring nitrogen of that thioether core with the bicyclic 2-bromoacetamide to deliver the exact target, CCOC(=O)c1cccc(Sc2c(Cl)n(CC(=O)N3CC4(CCC4)c4ccccc43)c3c(F)c(Cl)ccc23)c1F.

